==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: costusroot
<hw>costusroot</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>an annual herb (<spn>Saussurea
costus</spn>) of the eastern Himalayas (Kashmir) having purple florets
and a fragrant root that yields a volatile oil used in perfumery and for
preserving furs.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> <spn>Saussurea costus</spn>, Saussurea
lappa.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

